lippines]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language television programs]]\n\n{{Philippines-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2004 Philippine television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Te Amo, Maging Sino Ka Man\n| image = Te Amo, Maging Sino Ka Man title card.jpg\n| caption = Title card\n| show_name_2 = Te Amo, Speaking the Language of Love\n| genre = {{plain list|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Romance film|Romance]]}}\n| runtime = 30-45 minutes\n| creator = [[RJ Nuevas]]\n| company = GMA Entertainment TV\n| director = {{plain list|\n* Khryss Adalia\n* Lore Reyes}}\n| writer = {{plain list|\n* [[Suzette Doctolero]]\n* Joseph Balboa}}\n| executive_producer = Redgynn Alba\n| creative_director = [[Jun Lana]]\n| cinematography = Rhino Vidanes\n| starring = {{plainlist|\n* [[Iza Calzado]]\n* [[Segundo Cernadas]]}}\n| theme_music_composer = Tata Betita\n| composer = [[Rey Valera]]\n| opentheme = \"Maging Sino Ka Man\" by Nyoy Volante and Arnee Hidalgo\n| country = [[Philippines]]\n| location = {{plain list|\n* [[Quezon City]], Philippines\n* [[Ternate, Cavite]], Philippines}}\n| language = {{plain list|\n* [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]\n* [[Spanish language|Spanish]]\n* [[English language|English]]}}\n| network = [[GMA Network]]\n| picture_format = [[480i]] ([[SDTV]])\n| camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| first_aired = {{start date|2004|2|2}}\n| last_aired = {{end date|2004|9|17}}\n| num_episodes = 162\n}}\n\n'''''Te Amo, Maging Sino Ka Man''''' (International title: ''Te Amo, Speaking the Language of Love'' / {{translation|I Love You, Whoever You Are}}) is a 2004 [[Philippine television drama]] romance series broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. Directed by Khryss Adalia and Lore Reyes, it stars [[Iza Calzado]] and [[Segundo Cernadas]]. It premiered on February 2, 2004 on the network's Telebabad line up. The series concluded on September 17, 2004 with a total of 162 episodes.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{