{"title_page": "Walang Hanggan (2003 TV series)", "text_new": "{{short description|Philippine television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{for|the 2012 TV series|Walang Hanggan (2012 TV series)}}\n{{Infobox television\n| name = Walang Hanggan\n| show_name_2 = ''Eternity''\n| genre = {{plain list|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Romance film|Romance]]}}\n| picture_format = [[480i]] ([[SDTV]])\n| runtime = 30 minutes\n| company = [[TAPE Inc.|Television and Production Exponents Inc.]]\n| director = [[Gina Alajar]]\n| writer = [[RJ Nuevas]]\n| executive_producer = {{plainlist|\n* Antonio P. Tuviera\n* Malou Choa-Fagar}}\n| producer = Antonio P. Tuviera\n| starring = {{plain list|\n* [[Valerie Concepcion]]\n* [[Oyo Boy Sotto]]}}\n| theme_music_composer = [[Janno Gibbs]]\n| opentheme = \"Walang Hanggan\" by [[Janno Gibbs]]\n| country = [[Philippines]]\n| location = Philippines\n| language = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]\n| network = [[GMA Network]]\n| camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| first_aired = {{start date|2003|11|10}}\n| last_aired = {{end date|2004|2|27}}\n| num_episodes = 80\n}}\n\n'''''Walang Hanggan''''' (International title: ''Eternity'' / {{translation|No End}}) is a [[Philippine television drama]] romance series broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. Directed by [[Gina Alajar]], it stars [[Valerie Concepcion]] and [[Oyo Boy Sotto]]. It premiered on November 10, 2003 replacing ''[[Hawak Ko Ang Langit]]''. The series concluded on February 27, 2004 with a total of 80 episodes. It was replaced by ''[[Ikaw sa Puso Ko]]'' in its timeslot.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{multiple image\n|direction = vertical\n|align = right\n|image1 = ValerieConcepcionSMRosales20100711.jpg\n|caption1 = Valerie Concepcion portrays Almira.\n|width1 = 150\n}}\n\n;Lead cast\n*[[Valerie Concepcion]] as Almira\n*[[Oyo Boy Sotto]] as Basti\n*[[Iya Villania]] as Rachelle\n*Andrew Schimmer as Emil\n\n;Supporting cast\n*[[Miko Sotto]] as Mike\n*[[Zoren Legaspi]]\n*[[Sharmaine Arnaiz]]\n*[[Perla Bautista]]\n*Mikel Campos\n*Marissa Sanchez\n*Teri Onor\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0403822}}\n\n[[Category:GMA Network drama series]]\n[[Category:2003 Philippine television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2004 Philippine television series endings]]\n[[Category:Philippine drama television series]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Television series by TAPE Inc.]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language television programs]]\n\n{{Philippines-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Philippine television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{for|the 2012 TV series|Walang Hanggan (2012 TV series)}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Walang Hanggan\n| show_name_2 = Eternity\n| genre = {{plain list|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Romance film|Romance]]}}\n| picture_format = [[480i]] ([[SDTV]])\n| runtime = 30 minutes\n| company = [[TAPE Inc.|Television and Production Exponents Inc.]]\n| director = [[Gina Alajar]]\n| writer = [[RJ Nuevas]]\n| executive_producer = {{plainlist|\n* Antonio P. Tuviera\n* Malou Choa-Fagar}}\n| producer = Antonio P. Tuviera\n| starring = {{plain list|\n* [[Valerie Concepcion]]\n* [[Oyo Boy Sotto]]}}\n| theme_music_composer = [[Janno Gibbs]]\n| opentheme = \"Walang Hanggan\" by [[Janno Gibbs]]\n| country = [[Philippines]]\n| location = Philippines\n| language = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]\n| network = [[GMA Network]]\n| camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| first_aired = {{start date|2003|11|10}}\n| last_aired = {{end date|2004|2|27}}\n| num_episodes = 80\n}}\n\n'''''Walang Hanggan''''' (International title: ''Eternity'' / {{translation|No End}}) is a [[Philippine television drama]] romance series broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. Directed by [[Gina Alajar]], it stars [[Valerie Concepcion]] and [[Oyo Boy Sotto]]. It premiered on November 10, 2003 replacing ''[[Hawak Ko Ang Langit]]''. The series concluded on February 27, 2004 with a total of 80 episodes. It was replaced by ''[[Ikaw sa Puso Ko]]'' in its timeslot.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{multiple image\n|direction = vertical\n|align = right\n|image1 = ValerieConcepcionSMRosales20100711.jpg\n|caption1 = Valerie Concepcion portrays Almira.\n|width1 = 150\n}}\n\n;Lead cast\n*[[Valerie Concepcion]] as Almira\n*[[Oyo Boy Sotto]] as Basti\n*[[Iya Villania]] as Rachelle\n*Andrew Schimmer as Emil\n\n;Supporting cast\n*[[Miko Sotto]] as Mike\n*[[Zoren Legaspi]]\n*[[Sharmaine Arnaiz]]\n*[[Perla Bautista]]\n*Mikel Campos\n*Marissa Sanchez\n*Teri Onor\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0403822}}\n\n[[Category:GMA Network drama series]]\n[[Category:2003 Philippine television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2004 Philippine television series endings]]\n[[Category:Philippine drama television series]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Television series by TAPE Inc.]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language television programs]]\n\n{{Philippines-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Hotwiki", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Walang_Hanggan_(2003_TV_series)"}
